President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring September 2016 as National Childhood Obesity Awareness Month. The proclamation emphasizes the immediate and long-term health effects of childhood obesity and highlights the collaborative efforts that have been made to combat this issue. The proclamation recognizes the importance of fostering environments that support healthy choices and providing families with the knowledge and resources to make smart decisions. It also highlights various programs and initiatives, such as First Lady Michelle Obama's Let's Move! initiative, that aim to promote healthier lifestyles for children. The proclamation mentions the importance of nutrition and physical activity, including efforts to improve the quality of school meals and snacks and to encourage children to be more physically active. Overall, the proclamation calls on all Americans to take part in activities that promote healthy eating and physical activity for children.